	#. In a cubic room, let $T(x, y, z)$ be the temperature at the point $(x, y, z)$, where $x$ and $y$ are the distance from the southwestmost corner of the room in meters and $z$ is the distance up from the floor. What is the physical interpretation of $T_x(1, 1, 0)$? Do you expect $T_z(1, 1, 0)$ to be positive or negative? Explain.

